This paper presents a novel algorithm for multi-agent navigation using deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses a three-layer CNN, which involves training a neural network, and thus falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of motion information maps, which can be considered as a form of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the algorithm is designed to handle raw sensor measurements, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents a new approach that unifies local and global collision avoidance, which can be considered as a form of machine learning (cs.LG).
